003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Only seen by Gualtherus, and while Franz' amendment is attractive, it is difficult to see how exactly that is recovered from Gualtherus' transcription. Tortorici suggests that the inscription may not be genuine, a result of antiquarian enthusiasm to attribute the ruins as the temple, although this would be a relatively early date for such invention.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 31 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Amico 1741 236 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.1, no.20 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 cl.1, no.22 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5649e \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">449\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Tortorici 2016 65 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003